metadata.name: Secrets
metadata.description:
Tell me something
that you are scared to admit
you know the thing I'm talking about
That troubling truth
that would make society frown
That heartbreaking ache
that you may never get over
That deep desire,
the carnal craving,
that feels almost foreign yet you continue to long for it
Share with me
Shock or surprise me
but trust me
for I have secrets
too
Original poem by Margaret Lipsey


Photo and poem were part of my 100 day project in 2021 which was an exploration of my sensuality in middle age, the things I have learned, and the dreams that I continue to have.

Photo is approx 1800x2400px
